sql:
SELECT team_id, AVG(turnovers) AS average_turnovers
FROM drives
GROUP BY team_id;

external_knowledge:
- "handled the ball the roughest" indicates teams with the most turnovers; 
- "latest set of games" refers to the recent drives;
- "top ten most error-prone crews" means the ten teams with the highest total turnovers;
- "stars and their squads" represent the players' names and their team names.

- "treading the field of battle" refers to being an active player;
- "sailed through at least five battles" means a player has participated in at least five games;
- "under the banner of their respective teams" indicates the team the player belongs to.

- Significant number of drives refers to more than 50 drives;
- Last year refers to the year 2022;
- Most to least effective is based on higher to lower average yards gained per drive.
